    \begin{bmatrix} \rule[-3mm]{0pt}{9mm}\dfrac{6}{13} & \dfrac{6}{13} \\[8pt] \dfrac{1}{3} & \dfrac{1}{3}\rule[-3mm]{0pt}{9mm}  \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} a \\ b \end{bmatrix} &= \bm{0}  \hspace{3em} \left[\text{by letting } \bm{X}_1 = \begin{bmatrix} a \\ b \end{bmatrix}\right] \\[4pt]
    \begin{bmatrix}  \rule[-3mm]{0pt}{9mm}\dfrac{6a}{13} + \dfrac{6b}{13}\\[8pt]  \dfrac{a}{3} + \dfrac{b}{3}\rule[-3mm]{0pt}{9mm}  \end{bmatrix}&= \bm{0} \\[8pt]
    a + b &= 0 \\[8pt]
    a &= -b
    \end{align*}
    $$

    Hence we get $\tcbhighmath{\bm{X}_1  = \begin{bmatrix} -1 \\  \,\,\,\,\,1 \end{bmatrix}} \hspace{3em} [\text{by choosing } b = 1]$
    For $\lambda_2 = 1$, we have

    $$
    \begin{align*}
    \ \hspace{3cm}
